title: Football roundup: Waverly and Chillicothe win
text:
Football roundup: Waverly and Chillicothe win 12:30 a.m. EDT October 24, 2015 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Waverly 26, Minford 14 
Waverly (4-5) beat Minford at home on Friday. Drew Harris rushed for 127 yards and two touchdowns while Clayton Howell passed for 197 yards and two touchdowns. Cade Marquez caught six passes for 140 yards and two touchdowns. 
Zane Trace 44, Huntington 0 
Zane Trace (8-0, 6-0) won big on the road in a Scioto Valley Conference game. Austin Harris led the Pioneers, completing five passes for 118 yards and two touchdowns while also rushing for 98 yards. 
Joel Dunkle rushed for 50 yards and a touchdown while Drew Rittenhouse rushed for 49 yards and a touchdown. Timmy Gibson and Alex Wolff each had a touchdown reception. 
Huntington (1-8, 1-5) was led by Brian Smith with 53 yards rushing. 
Chillicothe 47, Washington Court House 9 
Chillicothe (6-3, 4-2) won big on the road in a South Central Ohio League game. Nate Rosenbauer led the Cavaliers, rushing for 134 yards and three touchdowns. 
Branden Maughmer passed for 48 yards and a touchdown while also rushing for 50 yards and a touchdown. Quintin Davidson caught three passes for 44 yards and a touchdown. 
Westfall 42, Southeastern 36 
Westfall won at home in a Scioto Valley Conference game. Matt Jude led the Mustangs, passing for 137 yards and a touchdown while also rushing for 81 yards and two touchdowns. 
Tyler Armentrout rushed for 109 yards and two touchdowns while Mason Peart caught three passes for 95 yards and a touchdown. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1S1SPkz TOP VIDEOS
